originalText.text: Superb service. I first came in to estimate a simple 11 page lamination job. First impressions: super friendly guys, the managers are awesome fun laid back guys having a great time & since I have to walk across the factory floor to get to the office, I can tell all the workers are happy, relaxed but productive, enjoying their work, and feeling good. You can feel the good vibe in this place. Now to the job: laminating as you may know has a few ordering details: thickness, finish quality, edge ("lip"), etc. They quickly explained the needed details, I went off to make the necessary new copies, brought them back, and easily submitted the job order. Aladdin's a printer for the corporate big large print run types but they were able to accommodate our relatively very small order of 22 pages at a price $1.81 or 40% less than Staples (4min walk away @ 500 8th Av for $3.39/pg) or ABC Imaging (3min walk away @ 336 W 37th S for $3.49/pg). Happy folks, great work, good company, great price, for what more could I ask? Thanks, guys!
